quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  25,56,"And We have not sent you (O dear Prophet Mohammed – peace and blessings be upon him) except as a Herald of glad tidings and warnings."
  25,57,"Proclaim, “I do not ask any fee from you for this, except that whoever wills may take the way to his Lord.”"
  25,58,"And trust the Living One Who will never die, and praising Him proclaim His Purity; and He is Sufficient upon the sins of His bondmen, All Aware."
  25,59,"The One Who created the heavens and the earth and all that is between them in six days, then befitting His Majesty, established Himself upon the Throne (of control); the Most Gracious – therefore ask the one who knows, concerning Him!"
  25,60,"And when it is said to them, “Prostrate to the Most Gracious” – they say, “And what is the Most Gracious? Shall we prostrate to whatever you command us?” And this command only increases the hatred in them. (Command of Prostration # 7)"
  25,61,"Most Auspicious is He Who created lofty towers in the sky and placed a lamp in it, and the luminous moon."
  25,62,"And it is He Who created the alternation of the night and day for one who wishes to remember or intends to give thanks."
  25,63,"And the bondmen of the Most Gracious who walk upon the earth humbly, and when the ignorant address them they answer, “Peace”. (Good –bye)"
  25,64,"And who spend the night prostrating and standing, for their Lord."
  25,65,"And who submit, “Our Lord – avert the punishment of hell from us; indeed its punishment is a permanent neck-shackle.”"
  25,66,"Indeed it is a most wretched abode."
  25,67,"And those who, when spending, neither exceed the limits nor act miserly, and stay in moderation between the two."
